Blurb::
Approach for addressing model misordering during numerical solutions.

Description::
Multifidelity Monte Carlo is a hierarchical sampling method that
requires an ordered set of quantities of interest (QoI) from the set
of model approximations, whether in terms of QoI correlations (for
analytic solutions) or model sample allocations (for estimator
variance calculations in numerical solutions).  In the latter case of
numerical solutions, ordering of sample allocations can be
accomplished using two different approaches, either reordering on the
fly ("auto_reorder") as dictated by a given set of allocations or
enforcing a prescribed model ordering ("fixed_order") through
additional linear constraints on the allocation solution.

